Maps are inherently unordered.  As has been suggested, `LinkedHashMap` preserves the insertion order.  There are many ways to accomplish this including yours.  Here are two of the same except one uses `Map&lt;String,Integer&gt;` the other uses `Map&lt;Character,Integer&gt;`

The Map.merge function takes the `key` (what your counting), and a value.  If the key is absent or the value is null, null is replaced by the value for the given key.  Otherwise, the value is remapped using the mapping function `(Integer::sum)` using the supplied value `(1)`.

Given
```
 String value = &quot;aaaaacccbbbbaaa&quot;;
